  "prompt": "I have a problem with coupon set up. I have created a coupon in WooCommerce and I want it to be applied to the product on sale. I have also removed the check from the exclude sale item. But still it's not applying that coupon to products which are on sale. How can I fix it?",
  "response": "Let's troubleshoot why your WooCommerce coupon isn't applying to sale items even though you've removed the \"Exclude Sale Items\" restriction. Here's a breakdown of potential issues and how to address them:\n\n**1. Double-Check \"Exclude Sale Items\"**\n\n*   **Go back to the coupon settings:** Seriously, double-check. Navigate to the WooCommerce coupon in your admin panel and ensure the \"Exclude Sale Items\" checkbox is *definitely* **unchecked**.  Sometimes a simple oversight is the culprit.\n*   **Save Changes:** Make sure you *saved* the coupon after unchecking the box.\n\n**2. Usage Restrictions & Conditions**\n\n*   **\"Products\" or \"Product Categories\":**  If you've specified particular products or product categories in the \"Products\" or \"Product Categories\" fields within the \"Usage Restriction\" tab, ensure the sale product(s) in question are actually included in this list.  A common mistake is restricting the coupon to only a few items, inadvertently excluding the sale item.\n*   **Minimum Spend:**  Does the cart meet the minimum spend requirement for the coupon to be valid?  Even if the sale item makes the total amount less, you still need to meet that minimum *before* the coupon is applied.\n*   **Maximum Spend:**  Is the cart *exceeding* the maximum spend allowed for the coupon?\n*   **Individual Use Only:** If the \"Individual Use Only\" box is checked, the coupon cannot be used in conjunction with other coupons.  Make sure there aren't other discounts or coupons already in the cart.\n*   **Exclude Sale Items (Again!):** While you've looked at the main \"Exclude Sale Items\" checkbox, make *absolutely* sure there's no hidden or misconfigured setting in a product category that would impact sales on items.\n*   **Allowed Emails (Usage Restriction):** Is the coupon restricted to specific email addresses? If so, make sure you're logged in with an account using one of those emails.\n\n**3. Coupon Validity & Limits**\n\n*   **Coupon Expiry Date:**  Has the coupon expired?  Check the \"Usage Limits\" tab for an expiration date.\n*   **Usage Limit per Coupon:** Has the coupon reached its overall usage limit?  (e.g., \"Usage limit per coupon\" is set to 10 and 10 people have already used it).\n*   **Usage Limit per User:** Has the user (you, or the test user) already used the coupon the maximum number of times allowed (\"Usage limit per user\" is set).\n\n**4. Theme or Plugin Conflicts**\n\n*   **Deactivate Plugins:** Temporarily deactivate *all* plugins except WooCommerce.  Then, test if the coupon now works.  If it does, reactivate plugins one by one, testing after each activation, to identify the conflicting plugin. Pay special attention to:\n    *   **Coupon Plugins:**  Any plugin that enhances or modifies WooCommerce coupons could be interfering.\n    *   **Pricing Plugins:** Plugins that manage dynamic pricing, bulk discounts, or similar features can sometimes conflict with coupons.\n    *   **Caching Plugins:**  Caching can sometimes lead to outdated coupon data being displayed. Clear your cache *after* making any changes to the coupon settings.\n*   **Theme Compatibility:**  While less likely, your theme *could* be interfering with the coupon functionality. Temporarily switch to a default WordPress theme like \"Twenty Twenty-Three\" or \"Twenty Twenty-Four\" and test again.  If the coupon works, the issue is with your theme.\n\n**5. Caching Issues**\n\n*   **Server-Side Caching:** If you have server-side caching enabled (e.g., through a hosting provider or a caching plugin), clear the server-side cache.\n*   **Browser Cache:** Clear your browser's cache.\n*   **WooCommerce Transients:** Go to `WooCommerce > Status > Tools` and clear your \"WooCommerce transients\".\n\n**6. Check WooCommerce Status**\n\n*   **Go to WooCommerce > Status:** Look for any errors or warnings that might indicate a problem with your WooCommerce installation.\n\n**7. Database Corruption**\n\n*   This is a less common, but potentially serious issue. While rare, your database might be corrupt. Contact your host to determine if a check and/or restore is appropriate.\n\n**8. Testing Methodology**\n\n*   **Incognito/Private Browsing:** Always test coupons in an incognito/private browsing window to avoid browser cache and cookie issues.\n*   **Different Browsers:** Test in multiple browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari) to rule out browser-specific problems.\n*   **Test Account:** Create a test user account to simulate a new customer's experience.\n*   **Clear Cart:** Ensure the cart is empty before each test.\n*   **Simple Products:** Start with a single, simple product (not a variable product) to eliminate any potential complexities.\n\n**9. Code Snippets (Advanced)**\n\n*   **If you're comfortable with code:** Some themes or plugins might have code snippets that override the default coupon behavior. Check your theme's `functions.php` file or any custom plugin files for code related to coupons or pricing.\n\n**Debugging Steps (for developers or if you're comfortable with code):**\n\n*   **`wc_coupon_is_valid()` Filter:** The `wc_coupon_is_valid` filter is used to determine if a coupon is valid.  You can use `add_filter` to hook into this filter and debug why the coupon is returning `false`.\n\n    ```php\n    add_filter( 'woocommerce_coupon_is_valid', 'my_coupon_debug', 10, 2 );\n    function my_coupon_debug( $valid, $coupon ) {\n      if ( ! $valid ) {\n        error_log( 'Coupon ' . $coupon->get_code() . ' is invalid.  Reasons:' );\n        error_log( print_r( $coupon->get_data(), true ) ); // Dump all coupon data\n        error_log( print_r( WC()->cart->get_cart_contents(), true ) ); // Dump cart contents\n        // Add more checks here, e.g., check if minimum spend is met.\n      }\n      return $valid;\n    }\n    ```\n\n    This code snippet will log details to your server's error log (usually `wp-content/debug.log`) if the coupon is considered invalid.  Check this log for clues.\n\n**Example Scenario and Solution**\n\nLet's say you've created a coupon called \"SUMMER20\" for 20% off, and you've verified \"Exclude Sale Items\" is *unchecked*.  You added a product that's currently on sale to the cart.  The coupon isn't working.\n\n1.  **Double-Check Products/Categories:**  Go to the coupon settings.  Under \"Usage Restriction,\" if you've listed any specific product IDs or category IDs, *make sure* the product you added to the cart is in that list.  **If the list is empty, this is probably NOT the issue.**\n2.  **Minimum Spend:**  If the \"Minimum spend\" is set to $50, and the *sale* price of your item is $40, the coupon won't apply until the cart total reaches $50 *before* the discount.\n3.  **Expiry Date:** Check that the coupon isn't expired.\n\nIf you've gone through all of these steps, please provide the following information so I can assist you further:\n\n*   **Coupon Code:** (e.g., SUMMER20)\n*   **Coupon Type:** (Percentage discount, Fixed cart discount, Fixed product discount)\n*   **Discount Amount:** (e.g., 20, 10)\n*   **Screenshot of the \"General\" tab of the coupon settings.**\n*   **Screenshot of the \"Usage Restriction\" tab of the coupon settings.**\n*   **Screenshot of the \"Usage Limits\" tab of the coupon settings.**\n*   **Example of a product that's on sale that the coupon *should* apply to (including product ID).**\n*   **List of plugins you have activated.**\n*   **Your WooCommerce version and PHP version.** (You can find this on the WooCommerce > Status page).\n*   **Is your theme custom built, or purchased? If purchased, what is the name of the theme?**\n\nWith this information, I can give you more targeted advice. Good luck!\n",
